programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Cynthia Rothrock
programme.desc: Officially named, “Queen of the Martial Arts,” Cynthia Rothrock is considered one of the most historic figures in martial arts history. or five consecutive years, she was the undefeated World Champion in the karate tournament circuit. She has graced the cover of over 60 martial arts magazines and was inducted into the prestigious Martial Arts History Museum’s Hall of Fame at its inception in 1999. In the 1980s, she became one of the biggest box office draws in both Hong Kong and America for her action films. To date, she has starred in over 60 films and was also named “Queen of the Martial Arts in Films”. She continues to be one of the greatest advocates for the martial arts conducting countless seminars throughout the world.

programme.title: Martial Arts History Museum-Gerald Okamura
programme.desc: Officially called the "scariest man alive" by Black Belt magazine, we go behind the scenes of one of the most awesome Asian bad guys, Gerald Okamura. From his iconic role at the Hatchett Man in "Big Trouble in Little China," to his many appearances as an evil bad dude, we explore Gerald Okamura's history, his life and his legendary career as one of the top weapons experts in America. Gerald Okamura was inducted into the Martial Arts History Museum's Hall of Fame in 2003. Directed by William Ford with Director of Photography Jim Towns.

This oddity, which was originally distributed by Columbia Pictures, was directed by one of the most prolific low budget filmmakers in Hollywood history, Sam Newfield, a man with over 200 movies to his credit. Directed by John Cromwell (Dead Reckoning, The Prisoner of Zenda) with dialog by noir master James M. Cain, Algiers was an influence on everything from Pepe Le Pew cartoons to the making of Casablanca.

programme.title: Cosmo Jones, Crime Smasher
programme.desc: Cosmo Jones (Frank Graham) is a small town man who considers himself a detective after taking a correspondence course. When he visits the nearest big city to offer his services to the police, he stumbles across everything from gang wars to kidnappings. With some great comic personalities in the cast, including Edgar Kennedy and Mantan Moreland, this delightful Monogram comedy was directed by James Tinling (Mr. Moto's Gamble, Charlie Chan in Shanghai) and practically invents the term "Do it yourself detecting!"

programme.title: Gorilla Ship (1932)
programme.desc: Vengeance rides the sea in this Depression era melodrama. This tale of shipwrecks and infidelity stars Ralph Ince as Captain "Gorilla" Larson, plus Vera Reynolds and Reed Howes, with direction by B-movie ace Frank R. Strayer (best known for The Vampire Bat). The multi-plot screenplay is by George Waggner, who would go on to direct such classics as The Wolfman and The Fighting Kentuckian...

programme.title: Lady Frankenstein
programme.desc: When Dr. Frankenstein is killed by his own creation, his daughter and his lab assistant, Marshall, continue his work. Together, they attempt to create a monster even greater than the one that killed Dr. Frankenstein. (Color)

programme.title: Mission Accomplished
programme.desc: Short Documentary on the Flying Fortress Plane.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 27
programme.desc: Carol Burnett leads a series of comedic sketches guest starring Peter Lawford and Minnie Pearl.

programme.title: Season 26 Episode 131
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: You're Ahead, Mr. X
programme.desc: From the uncrowned king of industrial and educational training films, Jam Handy, comes this vintage 1950s short.

programme.title: What's New? Featuring Pat Boone
programme.desc: From the uncrowned king of industrial and educational training films, Jam Handy, comes this vintage 1950s short.

programme.title: The Monster from the Ocean Floor
programme.desc: Julie, an American on vacation in Mexico, spots a giant, one-eyed amoeba rising from the ocean, but when she tries to tell the authorities, no one believes her. She finally teams up with a marine biologist in an attempt to destroy it.

programme.title: Anatomy of a Psycho (1961)
programme.desc: Terrifying! A Psychotic Killer prowls the night! ... Will he be stopped before he kills again? Ronnie Burns (the son of TV favorites George Burns and Gracie Allen!) stars as Chet, a delusional young man boiling with rage after his brother is sentenced to death for murder. As his paranoid feelings increase, Chet decides to create some mayhem of his own, including arson! A cast of unknowns come together for this feature by Boris Petroff, who also directed the cult favorite, The Unearthly. Just sit back and enjoy watching poor Chet lose touch with reality!

programme.title: Night Tide
programme.desc: A young sailor falls in love with a mysterious woman, performing as a mermaid at the local carnival. He soon comes to suspect the girl might be a real mermaid, who draws men to a watery death during the full moon.

programme.title: Mind Over Murder
programme.desc: When a young woman suffers a series of nightmares involving a bald man, a government agent seeks to uncover the truth when a plane crash appears to involve the man in the woman's dreams.

programme.title: Door (1956)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Family
programme.desc: Sgt. Joe Friday and his partners methodically investigate crimes in Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Devil's Laughter (1959)
programme.desc: On death row, John Marriott claims he has seen how he will die - and it will not be on the gallows.

programme.title: Turntable (1958)
programme.desc: When Mike takes pictures of a crooked gambler, a gubernatorial candidate promises to put the gambler out of business if elected. Before anything can be done, however, the pictures have been stolen and used to make a composite that makes the candidate appear to be a member of the gambling syndicate.

programme.title: Badge Without Honor
programme.desc: After a U.S. deputy marshal saves Adam's life from two gunmen, he explains that he is in town to bring a close friend of the Cartwright's to San Francisco to testify in a statewide racketeering trial, but the Deputy Marshal's motives for the witness soon become suspicious.

programme.title: Duke Steals a Wife
programme.desc: This is the only episode of The Beverly Hillbillies to mention Jed's late wife and Elly May's mother.

programme.title: Disc Jockey
programme.desc: Mickey works as a Disc Jockey and becomes embroiled in the schemes of a group of thieves.

programme.title: The Case of the Perfect Husband
programme.desc: Holmes and Watson must devise a plan to trap a killer who confessed to his wife that he has killed all six of his previous wives, giving her limited time before she becomes his next victim.

programme.title: Boy in the Storm
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: Framed
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Opera Tickets
programme.desc: Stanley struggles to sell two tickets for the Metropolitan Opera after being scammed by a scalper.

programme.title: The Mink Coat
programme.desc: Just when Jim tells the family to cut down on spending, he jumps at a deal for Margaret on a mink coat.

programme.title: Colorado Kid (1966)
programme.desc: Cowboy star Bob Steele (Valley of Hunted Men, The Trail Blazers) headlines this Poverty Row western drama. As the Colorado Kid, he's falsely arrested for murder and has to clear himself. The colorful cast includes Ernie Adams, Frank LaRue, and Horace Murphy, with direction by Sam Newfield (The Terror of Tiny Town, The Mad Monster).

programme.title: Silks and Saddles
programme.desc: College student Jimmy Shaw has a winner in Lightning Lad, a racehorse he inherited. But after he turns down a spoiled rich girl who wants Lightning Lad for herself, he finds himself involved in more skullduggery than he'd ever imagined. Bruce Bennett (Mildred Pierce, Sahara) and Toby Wing (Search for Beauty) headline the cast, with direction by Robert F. Hill (Cowboy Holiday, Sundown Trail). Be sure to listen for a rendition of 'I Took My Girl to the Races' by everyone's favorite cowboy sidekick, Fuzzy Knight.

programme.title: Texas, Brooklyn and Heaven (1948)
programme.desc: When Eddie Tayloe (Guy Madison, 5 Against the House) receives $6,000 from his grandfather, he decides to leave his drab newspaper job and move to New York. His dream is to have a play produced on Broadway. Along the way he picks up a pretty hitchhiker (Diana Lynn, The Miracle of Morgan's Creek) who is also leaving her own dreary life for a shot at New York. Unfortunately, they find that the Big Apple is a hard place to make a living. But it's also a city where circumstances keep bringing them together!

programme.title: The Animal Kingdom (1932)
programme.desc: Ann Harding, Myrna Loy, and Leslie Howard star in this RKO drama about a love triangle. The film was based on a play by Philip Barry, one of the most revered writers in Hollywood, television, and Broadway history, whose work included The Philadelphia Story, Holiday, and Without Love. For trivia buffs: Legendary director George Cuckor went uncredited on this feature, though he stepped in to guide several scenes after official director Edward Griffith walked off the production.

programme.title: The Admiral Was A Lady (1950)
programme.desc: In this laugh-a-minute, post-World War II comedy, Wanda Hendrix (Prince of Foxes) stars as Jean Madison, a former WAVE (Women Accepted for Volunteer Emergency Service) ensign taken under the wings of a rowdy group of former airmen, who affectionately dub her the “Admiral.” Handily directed by veteran filmmaker Albert S. Rogell (Li’l Abner), the film is bolstered by the crackling chemistry between Hendrix and her co-star, Oscar winner Edmond O’Brien (The Barefoot Contessa).

programme.title: Hoppy Serves a Writ
programme.desc: Sheriff Hopalong Cassidy triumphs again in this lighthearted western romp from Harry Sherman Productions. Good ol' Happy (William Boyd) has to leave his beloved Texas to track down some bad guys in Oklahoma. You can bet that the action and suspense will follow Hopalong wherever he goes. Also, look for a number of familiar faces in the ast, including TV's future Superman George Reeves, notorious Hollywood heavy Victor Jory, and in his movie debut, Robert Mitchum!

programme.title: Too Late for Tears (1949)
programme.desc: Lizabeth Scott turned in what many consider her finest role in this shocking noir about a woman who finds herself in possession of stolen money. When a dangerous character named Danny Fuller (Dan Duryea) tracks her down and claims the money is his, she’s determined to hang onto her stash. Director Byron Haskin (I Walk Alone) brings together a fine cast that includes Don Defore and Arthur Kennedy, plus cinematography by two-time Oscar winner William C. Mellor (A Place in the Sun). If you’ve never seen this noir gem, you’re in for a hard­boiled treat!

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Alexa moved from New York City to small-town Jackson, Mississippi, to teach at an under-priveleged school. After only two weeks in, Alexa had to challenge homophobia in the hallway, and had some surprising success. Megan's grandma was supportive and excited when she found out Megan was a lesbian. But after showing signs of Alzheimer's, Megan's grandma forgot and kept asking her if she was seeing any special boy. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Jacob Tobia, activist for genderqueer, gender non-conforming, and transgender issues, bought a single pair of black pumps while organizing a Gender Nonconforming Day for their high school, a small act that would change the course of their life. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. - Externals

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: Her Story
programme.desc: S1 | Her Story is about two trans women in Los Angeles who have given up on love, when chance encounters give them hope. Violet is drawn to Allie, a reporter who approaches her for an interview. Career-driven Paige meets James, the first man she's considered opening up to in years. Will they risk letting what they are stand in the way of being loved for who they are? This is a story of complex characters who laugh, struggle, and grow, who share strength in sisterhood, who seek and find love. Her Story depicts the unique, complicated, and very human women we see in queer communities, and explores how these women navigate the intersections of label identity and love.

programme.title: Ali in the Valley | Easy French Onion Soup
programme.desc: This Easy French Onion Soup is rich, comforting and so good with toasted cheesy bread for dipping! What better way to kick off Season 4 of Ali in the Valley than with a delicious decadent classic French Onion Soup. French Onion Soup is such a classic and SO easy to make! Onions are slowly caramelized until soft and sweet, simmered with beef broth, and just a touch of sugar. It’s topped with crispy croutons, loads of shredded gruyere cheese, and broiled into crispy, cheesy oblivion. So good!

programme.desc: Dr. Proctor is a geoscientist, explorer, space artist, and astronaut. She is the mission pilot for the Inspiration4 all-civilian orbital mission to space. She is also one of The Explorer’s Club 50: Fifty People Changing the World. Her motto is called Space2inspire where she encourages people to use their unique, one-of-a-kind strengths, and passion to inspire those within their reach and beyond. She believes that we need to actively strive for a J.E.D.I. space: a just, equitable, diverse, and inclusive space as we advance human spaceflight.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Lets Get Lost
programme.desc: Jumping into a Thai tuk tuk taxi, Tony attempts to soak up Thai culture, and get lost in the cuisine of Chiang Mai, Thailand.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art
programme.desc: We'll ride a unicorn into the Middle Ages at Paris’ Cluny Museum, get a heavenly look at stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle, go on a tombstone pilgrimage at Pere Lachaise Cemetery, and savor the Parisian cafe scene.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.title: Switzerlands Amazing Train Rides
programme.desc: Join host Jeff Wilson and PBS award-winning photographers and ride through a Swiss Alps train adventure. The wonders of the Alps exhilarate travelers as you travel through stunning scenic routes and the iconic Matterhorn, a 14,600-foot peak that overlooks the charming town of Zermatt, Switzerland.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Ireland's West Coast
programme.desc: Our trip to Ireland's west coast begins in Galway, Europe's fastest growing city, shopping for Irish crystal and Celtic jewelry. Then it is a salt-sprayed trip to the fabled Aran Islands where we reach breathless heights at a Stone Age fort and ferret out traditional hand-knit sweaters.

programme.title: Dublin and Beyond
programme.desc: Irish eyes are smiling when we explore Dublin, Ireland's urban core. There is history around every corner, and Dublin delights with Trinity College, the Book of Kells, the famous Guinness Brewery, and the infamous Kilmainham jail where Irish rebels spent their last days.

programme.title: Germany's Romantic Road
programme.desc: The Romantic Road winds through some of Germany's most picturesque countryside complete with medieval villages and Baroque Palaces. We start our journey in Wurzburg where we visit the spectacular Baroque Bishop's Palace or Residenz and taste wine at one of Wurzburg's many wine festivals.

programme.title: Darwin Northern Territory
programme.desc: In Darwin, Jason swims in the Crocodile Tank and visits Litchfield National Park. He also goes heli-pubbing, savours the delicious barra burger, then catches, and cooks, black pepper mud crab. Delicious!

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: S8E1 - Mediterranean Baja
programme.desc: The Baja California peninsula boasts a climate reminiscent of the Mediterranean Sea. Rick makes tacos with ingredients from the gardens of the Rancho La Puerta spa, and meets up with Chefs Miguel Angel Guerrero Yagues and Jair Tellez.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: Ocho Rios, Jamaica
programme.desc: Donna visits Ocho Rios, Jamaica and explores the history, culture, adventure, and an amazing family-focused resort. She also highlights a wonderful Jam-Italian fusion restaurant that is a MUST when visiting Ocho Rios.

programme.title: Sea Change
programme.desc: Fresh water is one of Earth’s sacred resources. Lake Turkana’s freshwater resources are vital to countless people who rely on it for sustenance. When a dam threatened to disturb the Lake’s ecosystem, some took action to protect their home.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: The Volga, Soul of Russia
programme.desc: The Volga River, also called "matuschka,” welcomes world travelers on giant boats. Take a journey of 4,000 kilometers towards the Caspian Sea, from Moscow to Astrakhan, through Laroslav, Nijini Novgorod, Kazan, Samara, and Saratov.

programme.title: A Taste of Tokyo
programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S8E1 - Western Turkey
programme.desc: After kicking off in Kusadası, we wander ancient Ephesus, soak in a natural spa at Pamukkale, learn why dervishes whirl at Konya, and sail the Mediterranean on a "gulet" from Antalya.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Venice, the city of winding canals, decadent buildings, faith, and romance. Tour Piazza San Marco and the Basilica of San Marco. Visit a mask shop, then ship off to the islands of Murano, Burano and Torcello. Venice’s very existence, floating as if on a dream, is an amazing experience to behold.

programme.title: S8E12 - Berlin
programme.desc: While visiting Berlin's powerful sights — moving memorials, top-tier museums, surviving bits of communist and fascist days — we'll take time to revel in its vibrant social scene.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: Miami
programme.desc: Bienvenido a Miami! We look at the history behind Florida's modern metropolis. We visit the Ancient Spanish Monastery, see the opulence of the Vizcaya Museum and Gardens, and head into the swamp to learn about the Miccosukee Indians.

programme.title: Sydney New South Wales
programme.desc: In Sydney, Jason takes part in some cooking at the award-winning Marque restaurant and meets with an up-and-coming pastry chef at The Blackstar Pastry. For some fun activities, he tries grape stomping and quad biking.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Most Unusual Festivals
programme.desc: When it is festival time, it is FUN time. Join Will Clinger and travel coast to coast to discover America’s most unique, enlightening, and unusual festivals. Get in the spirit, celebrate life, and pay homage to our shared cultural history.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: S8E7 - Cooking in Wine Country
programme.desc: Ever dream of owning a winery? Don and Tru Miller made their dreams come true when they built Adobe Guadalupe. Rick’s dream of cooking in their stunning kitchen, with its handmade wood-fired oven, comes true this season. Dream on.

programme.title: S8E8 - Tijuana Round Table
programme.desc: There is a long heritage of good food in Tijuana. The city has an amazing taco, culture and is the birthplace of the Caesar salad. Today, Tijuana boasts one of the top culinary schools in the country and some of the best chefs in Mexico.

programme.title: S8E9 - Extraordinarily Delicious Ensenada
programme.desc: Fish tacos embody Ensenada’s history: Fresh fish from pristine waters encased in crispy batter influenced by Asian immigrants, topped with Spanish-inspired creamy sauces, wrapped in a very Mexican corn tortilla, and spiked with chile.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: S8E11 - Sustainable Aquaculture in the Rich Waters of Ensenada
programme.desc: Two of Ensenada’s best chefs, Benito Molina, and Alain Genchi, join Rick for a lesson in mollusk farming. Juan Carlos Lapuente takes the trio to the rich coastal waters to see oyster and mussel farming and learn why these waters thrive.

programme.title: Montego Bay, Jamaica
programme.desc: Donna visits Montego Bay and Negril where she will continue her journey into the heart of Jamaica. Join her as she visits the Rose Hall Great House with its mysterious past, Half Moon Resort, and takes part in cliff diving and zip lining.

programme.title: From Chicago to the Karoo
programme.desc: A healthy mind, body, and environment are all critical for living happy and productive lives. Meet pioneering people in Iraq, Colombia, South Africa, Indonesia, the United States, and Italy who believe in living symbiotically with nature.

programme.title: From Guatemala to the Congo
programme.desc: Stewardship of the land is a central part of the human condition. Unfortunately, in some cases, so is greed. Meet people from California, Congo, India, Australia, Guatemala, and Slovenia whose spirit matches their intent to live healthily.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Livingstone
programme.desc: “The Road of Livingstone” is a long journey in the footsteps of the British explorer David Livingstone along the Zambezi River, from its mouth in Mozambique all the way to Victoria Falls, at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey
programme.desc: In Turkey, we'll marvel at the fascinating landscape of Cappadocia from high above in a balloon...and from deep below, prowling an underground city where Christians once hid out.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Madrid
programme.desc: The Spanish capital Madrid welcomes us with grand plazas and sparkling fountains. First stop is the Prado, one of Europe's great museums and home to Goya, El Greco and Velazquez.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Belize
programme.desc: Un-Belizable! We are off on a Central American Mayan excursion. We head up the steps of the ancient high temple at Lamanai. Then we take a city tour of the main tourist destination, Belize City. We learn about Belize's colonial roots at the Belize City History Museum and dive the amazing Blue Hole.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Disneyland Resort: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: It was Walt Disney’s original vision that Disneyland would “never be completed” – always growing and changing. Decades later, Disneyland remains one of the most visited destinations on Earth. Disney Parks has proven its ability remain relevant and continue to be at the very top of the theme parks.

programme.title: The Glacier Express and Gornergrat-Bahn
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: S9E4 - Artisan Mescal
programme.desc: Mescal is experiencing a renaissance in Mexico and throughout the United States. Journey with Rick to witness firsthand how an Oaxacan distiller handcrafts this fine spirit renowned for its rich, smoky complexity and brightness.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: Montreal, Canada
programme.desc: Join Donna in Montreal and experience the cultural and Epicurean wonders found in this amazing city in Quebec. Also, go jet boating and learn why Montreal is the unofficial "world headquarters" for the circus arts.

programme.title: From Ithaca to the Amazon
programme.desc: Our natural environments are intrinsically more valuable than any grand visions of wealth created using methods detrimental to the Earth. Meet people in New York, India, Russia, Peru, Sumatra, and South Africa who favor health over profit.

programme.title: From Hanoi to Paris
programme.desc: The value of Earth’s natural resources changes depending on to whom you speak. Meet people from France, Colombia, Vietnam, South Africa, the Philippines, and Michigan who have circumvented extraordinary challenges to protect the Earth.

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S8E3 - France’s Loire: Chateau Country
programme.desc: In France's Loire Valley, we'll visit four unique castles — elegant Chenonceau, massive Chambord, stately Cheverny, and fragrant Villandry — with fun stops along the way.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Edmonton, Canada
programme.desc: In the second part of her tour of Alberta, Canada, you and Donna will discover fresh cuisine at the local farmer's market and explore some of the region’s crafts. You will also go snowshoeing and learn how to ski.

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Four Great Cities of Europe
programme.desc: Explore the world class European cities of London, Paris, Amsterdam, and Brussels. A European city bustles. It is a hub of commerce, the arts, energy, surprise, and international flavor. Where do you start if you have just 24-hours?

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: Louisville
programme.desc: And we are off! We learn the history of the world famous Kentucky Derby, and call our shot, at one of America's most famous brands, Louisville Slugger. Also, we zip line in the world's only underground zip line attraction, and learn about Muhammad Ali's legacy at the Ali Center.

programme.title: Safe Harbor
programme.desc: Doug and Robbie are about to set sail on a long trip when they unexpectedly find themselves foster parenting a group of troubled teenage boys. The experience changes their lives for the better, and they decide to stay in town and run the foster home for boys permanently.

programme.title: Take Me Home: The John Denver Story
programme.desc: John Denver achieved fame, fortune, and acclaim for his iconic country-pop music, but his sunny personality masked private pain and dark secrets that his celebrity could never heal.

programme.title: The Rivals
programme.desc: David Nelson has a rival, and his name is Will Thornberry, the Nelson's next door neighbor.

programme.title: The Pills
programme.desc: Ozzie decides that he wants to go on a diet so that he can fit into a pair of size 33 pants.

programme.title: The Fall Guy
programme.desc: At first Ozzie, attempts to persuade his son David to stand up for his rights, and not allow people to take advantage of his good nature, after David has an argument with a friend. However, Ozzie quickly regrets the advice he gave David.

programme.title: Starcrossed Lovers
programme.desc: Parsons' good-hearted sidekick Ben is now a member of the Robinson family group, but David objects when he discovers that Ben is in love with his daughter Joanna. Meanwhile, Emily must act as midwife when Elizabeth prepares to give birth.

programme.title: Never Name a Duck
programme.desc: Ritchie becomes very attached to two baby ducks that were left over from a show and decides to adopt them. Rob faces the daunting task of making Ritchie understand the consequence of attempting to keep wild animals as pets that may be happier living in the wild.

programme.title: My Classic Car

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Hobie Fishing - Panama, Part 1
programme.desc: Hobie Outdoor Adventures flies down to the southernmost country of Central America, the Republic of Panama, and heads to a secluded coast with a lush rainforest coastline, where the only way to fish is from a kayak.

programme.title: Pro Vs Joe - South Florida Canals1
programme.desc: Brent Chapman’s Pro Vs Joe South Florida Canals1

programme.title: Pro vs Joe - Lake Apache
programme.desc: Brent Chapmans Pro Vs Joe Lake Apache

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - Bluefin Tuna and Yellowtail Fishing on the El Dorado
programme.desc: Shea McIntee and the crew take a two and a half-day trip on one of our all-time favorite charter boats, the El Dorado, out of Long Beach Sportfishing. We fish on San Clemente Island and venture offshore in search of tuna.

programme.title: VW Escarabajo
programme.desc: Hay un coche que todo el mundo conoce. Un coche al que se le ha dado un apodo y no se le ha vuelto a llamar de otra manera: El Escarabajo VW. Con mas de 60 anos de antiguedad, nos dice mas sobre nuestro siglo que muchos libros de historia. La Historia del Automovil cuenta la historia del escarabajo indestructible, desde el primer modelo de 24,5 CV hasta el ultimo modelo del Nuevo Escarabajo.

programme.title: Coupes alemanes
programme.desc: Diseno y tecnologia de vanguardia y placer de conduccion, ya sea el Porsche 911, el Mercedes Clase S Coupe, el BMW Serie 6 o el Audi RS5, los coupes alemanes estan entre los coches mas fascinantes del mundo. Con motores potentes, chasis deportivos y tecnologia avanzada, encarnan mas que ningun otro coche la conduccion apasionada. DreamCars presenta los cupes alemanes mas rapidos y bonitos.

programme.title: El Campeonato Aleman de Turismos
programme.desc: El campeonato aleman de coches de turismo de 1992: definitivamente una de las series de carreras mas importantes del deporte del motor aleman. Duro, despiadado y bien conocido por las duras batallas de sus despiadados competidores.

programme.title: Hans Herrmann
programme.desc: Durante los anos 50 y 70, Hans Herrmann se hizo famoso gracias a su exito como piloto de Formula 1 y de coches deportivos de fabricantes como Porsche, Mercedes-Benz y Maserati, ademas de ganar varias veces las 24 Horas de Le Mans.

programme.title: Normal vs. Lifestyle SUV
programme.desc: Los SUV Nissan X-Trail y BMW X4 no son los tipicos todoterreno. Asistimos a la presentacion del nuevo modelo X-Trail de Nissan y al estreno mundial del BMW X4 en Bilbao. Y tambien: el Trofeo Steinbeißer, con la participacion de todoterrenos en un emocionante rally.

programme.title: Ferrari
programme.desc: Ferrari... solo el nombre hace que tu corazon se acelere. Ya sea en la carretera o en la pista de carreras, dondequiera que el coche con el emblema del caballo saltarin ponga en marcha su rugiente motor, siempre sera el centro de atencion. La Historia del Automovil mostrara la historia de este corredor rojo de "Maranellesi" - desde el primer coche deportivo hasta el ultimo Ferrari FF.

programme.title: SUV americanos
programme.desc: En EE. UU., los SUV no se consideran como meros vehiculos de trabajo, sino mas bien como vehiculos de uso cotidiano. Los estadounidenses no renuncian al espacio, la comodidad y la capacidad de carga. Su lema es "cuanto mas grande, mejor". Chevrolet Suburban, Jeep Cherokee, GMC Yukon: les mostramos el mundo de los todoterrenos de EE. UU.

programme.title: Division Especial Motorizada de la Policia de Dubai
programme.desc: Por primera vez, la unidad de autos especiales de la Policia de Dubai permite que un equipo de television les acompane en una jornada de patrulla. Unos autos nada normales para una ciudad que tampoco tiene nada de normal.

programme.title: Episodio 1
programme.desc: Los presentadores invitan a los magnates de Oriente Medio a llevar sus coches tuneados al 'The Walk' en la playa de Jumeirah y a clasificarlos por su velocidad, estilo y sonido. Quien reciba mas puntos ganara una estancia de una noche para dos personas en el glamuroso Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach. En este episodio, un Chevrolet Camaro y un Mercedes SLS AMG intentaran sorprender.

programme.title: Descapotables alemanes
programme.desc: Ya sea el Porsche 911 Cabriolet, el Audi R8 Spyder o el Mercedes SLS AMG Roadster, los descapotables alemanes gozan de una reputacion mundial. Son famosos por su perfeccion y fiabilidad. Son considerados como la encarnacion del estatus y como la expresion del estilo de vida y la alegria de vivir. DreamCars presenta los descapotables alemanes mas emocionantes, mas bonitos y mas rapidos.

programme.title: 50 anos de Porsche 911
programme.desc: El Porsche 911. Estos tres numeros representan la leyenda, el mito y el sentimiento. Un motor V6 trasero boxer y un diseno unico lo convierten en un coche deportivo iconico. La Historia del Automovil explica el secreto de este vehiculo, que forma la base de las nuevas generaciones: desde el modelo original 911 de 1963 con 130 caballos hasta el GT2 RS con 620 caballos y el ultimo modelo 911 (991).

programme.title: Pikes Peak 1987
programme.desc: La subida a la colina de Pikes Peak de 1987. Un tipo de carrera bastante diferente en las montanas de Colorado, EE.UU.. Es unica, fascinante y llena de aventura.

programme.title: Episodio 2
programme.desc: Si quieres ver vehiculos de lujo o tuneados nunca vistos, tienes que ir a "The Walk", el glamuroso bulevar de Jumeirah Beach. Put Your Car on TV invita a los propietarios a que sus vehiculos sean valorados por Saif Hattawi. La persona con mas puntos ganara un regalo especial del Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach. Entre los coches presentados estan un BMW X5 y un Mercedes SLK 230.

programme.title: Ferruccio Lamborghini
programme.desc: En el municipio de Sant'Agata Bolognese se encuentran las raices de la emblematica marca italiana Lamborghini. En 1964, Ferruccio Lamborghini se propuso construir los mejores coches deportivos del mundo, un osado proyecto al hallarse a pocos kilometros de Ferrari. A pesar de eso, su primer modelo, el 350 GT, dejo atras a la competencia de Maranello, al que le seguirian muchos otros.

programme.title: Salvajes por el desierto
programme.desc: En 2010, BMW y el equipo de carreras aleman X-Raid decidieron transformar el Mini Countryman en un vehiculo todoterreno y participar en el mundialmente famoso Rally Dakar. Y ademas: el Mercedes G63 AMG 6x6, el mas exclusivo todoterreno de 6 ruedas, muestra sus prestaciones en el desierto cerca de Dubai; el Kia Sportage se siente comodo tanto en el terreno rocoso de Sicilia como en la ciudad.

programme.title: Supercoches italianos
programme.desc: Los Supercoches Italianos son los coches mas emocionantes del mundo. Ya sea el Ferrari "La Ferrari", el Lamborghini Aventador o el Pagani Huayra, son los coches mas bonitos y rapidos del mundo, creados por los disenadores mas famosos. Los superdeportivos italianos son suenos de coches que se han hecho realidad. DreamCars presenta los supercoches italianos mas impresionantes.

programme.title: Audi Quattro
programme.desc: Es el coche que cambio el mundo de los coches: el Audi Quattro. Por primera vez, la traccion a las cuatro ruedas no solo se encuentra en un coche de serie, sino tambien en un coche de rallye. La Historia del Automovil muestra su historia desde el principio hasta el mas espectacular coche de Rallyes jamas construido, el S1. Walter Rohrl cuenta sus impresiones y experiencias con el Audi Quattro.

programme.title: Ferry Porsche
programme.desc: El nombre de la familia Porsche lleva ligado al diseno, la fabricacion y las carreras de coches desde principios del siglo XX. Tras la Segunda Guerra Mundial, y siguiendo los pasos de su padre que habia sido responsable de desarrollo del clasico Volkswagen, Ferry Porsche sento las bases de celebres modelos como el 356 y, mas tarde, del mitico Porsche 911.

programme.title: La ultima tendencia en SUV
programme.desc: Los Vehiculos Utilitarios Urbanos son la ultima tendencia en el mundo del automovil. No estan hechos para terreno sin asfaltar pero atraen a los clientes por su diseno moderno y urbano. En este episodio, el Subaru XV muestra sus habilidades offroad y el Nissan Juke es llevado a la pista de carreras en Dubai; el Mercedes-AMG y el Audi RS Q3 GLA se enfrentan en las montanas.

programme.title: BMW M3 E30
programme.desc: En 1986, nacio una leyenda: el BMW M3, uno de los coches de deportes de motor mas exitosos de la historia. Se sentia como en casa tanto en los deportes de motor como en la carretera. De 1987 a 1992 el M3 Turismo gano el Campeonato DTM dos veces, asi como varias otras competiciones internacionales. Con mas de 1.500 victorias y mas de 50 titulos de campeonato en 7 anos, el BMW M3 es el turismo mas exitoso del mundo.

programme.title: Episodio 3
programme.desc: La gente de Oriente Medio esta loca por sus coches. En Put Your Car on TV pueden presentar sus vehiculos tuneados y valorados. Se les otorgan puntos por la velocidad, el estilo y el sonido y el propietario con mas puntos gana un regalo especial para dos personas del Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach. Entre los competidores hay un Nova SS, un Honda Acord especial y un coche lleno de cristales.

programme.title: Coupes britanicos
programme.desc: Los coches deportivos ingleses son los clasicos entre los coupes, coches tan geniales como James Bond. Aston Martin, Bentley y Jaguar producen los cupes mas exclusivos y elegantes del mundo. Su diseno distintivo sigue inspirandose en los emblematicos Jaguar E-Type y Aston Martin DB5. DreamCars presenta los cupes ingleses mas exclusivos y caros.

programme.title: Chevrolet
programme.desc: Corvette, Camaro, Impala... ¿hay alguien que no sepa de estos coches de ensueno americanos? El foco de la historia del automovil de hoy es, por supuesto, la historia de la marca Chevrolet y el ultimo modelo de Chevrolet Corvette, asi como el mas reciente Chevrolet Camaro. Ademas, la historia de las carreras de Chevrolet, desde Le Mans hasta Indianapolis, con multiples entrevistas.

programme.title: Carreras del Gran Premio desde 1934
programme.desc: Desde 1934, el Gran Premio ha sido el campeonato mundial mas emocionante y fascinante del mundo. Con sus vehiculos de ultima generacion, con los caballos de potencia de las marcas mas grandes, nunca deja de impresionar a sus espectadores.

programme.title: Episodio 4
programme.desc: Continua la busqueda del coche mas rapido, bonito y con mejor sonido. Los amantes de los coches de Oriente Medio traen sus vehiculos tuneados al Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach y son evaluados por Saif Hattawi. El ganador recibe un regalo especial para dos personas en el lujoso Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach. Un Ford Mustang y un Chevrolet Corvette de edicion limitada tratan de ganar el concurso.

programme.title: Walther Roehrl
programme.desc: No se puede hablar de deportes de rally sin mencionar a Walter Rohrl. Desde muy joven, Rohrl demostro su talento ganando campeonatos europeos, mundiales e internacionales de rally. Para los apasionados de las carreras, se trata de una leyenda viva, un genio al volante.

programme.title: Limusinas britanicas
programme.desc: Las limusinas inglesas son la encarnacion del lujo, son irresistibles e impresionantes y son la clase alta automovilistica. Construidas con los materiales mas caros, las limusinas inglesas como el Rolls Royce Phantom, el Bentley Mulsanne o el Jaguar XJ combinan un lujo intemporal, un confort unico y una potencia superior. DreamCars presenta las mas exclusivas y costosas limusinas inglesas.

programme.title: Mercedes SL
programme.desc: Desde los anos 50 el Mercedes SL ha sido considerado la leyenda de los coches deportivos. Desde el legendario 300SL, la serie SL ha sido todo innovacion y deportividad. SL es la abreviatura alemana de Super Leicht - super ligero. Hoy en dia la abreviatura significa mas bien super lujo. Sin embargo, cada modelo ha establecido el punto de referencia para el diseno y la innovacion tecnica.

programme.title: Hans-Joachim Stuck
programme.desc: Hans-Joachim Stuck es uno de los mejores pilotos de carreras de Alemania y un verdadero icono del deporte automovilistico internacional. A lo largo de su trayectoria no solo ha ganado la Formula II y varios campeonatos internacionales, sino tambien la prestigiosa carrera 24 Horas de Le Mans en dos ocasiones, la primera de ellas cuando solo tenia 19 anos.

programme.title: Especial Land Rover
programme.desc: El Land Rover Defender es uno de los todoterrenos mas antiguos. Puede ser ruidoso e incomodo pero es totalmente genuino por su simplicidad. Echamos un vistazo a este vehiculo emblematico y a los 70 anos de historia del Land Rover. Y tambien: llevamos el Range Rover Evoque, el modelo mas reciente de la marca britanica, a la legendaria Ruta de la Seda.

programme.title: SUV extraordinarios
programme.desc: Este Mitsubishi Outlander Plug-In Hybrid es el primer SUV hibrido del mundo con dos motores electricos y un motor de dos litros. Probamos si tal combinacion tiene sentido para los vehiculos todoterreno. Y ademas: el Chevrolet Silverado es una camioneta americana con un V8 y un consumo medio de 15 litros aunque puede ahorrar dinero gracias a su motor de gas natural.

programme.title: BMW Kelleners Sport 640i Grand Coupe
programme.desc: El Kelleners Sport 640i es probablemente uno de los cupes de 4 puertas mas bellos en la actualidad. La compania de tuning de Ralf Kelleners, hijo del tres veces campeon europeo de turismos Helmut Kelleners, se hizo un nombre en el mundo del diseno e ingenieria y es el responsable especialista en la remodelacion de BMW.

programme.title: Episodio 5
programme.desc: Put Your Car on TV ofrece a los propietarios de coches la posibilidad de llevar sus vehiculos tuneados a la playa del Hotel Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah, donde Saif Hattawi los evaluara segun la velocidad, el estilo y el sonido. El premio es una estancia de una noche en el Sofitel Hotel Dubai Jumeirah Beach para dos personas. Compiten un BMW X6M, un enorme Ford F250 y un Nissan Patrol especial.

programme.title: Supercoches britanicos
programme.desc: Ya sea el Aston Martin Vanquish, el Bentley Continental GT Speed, el McLaren P1, los supercoches ingleses son los deportivos mas rapidos, espectaculares y bellos del mundo. No solo tienen potencia, sino tambien algo especial. Tienen gracia y velocidad gracias a sus cuerpos con forma aerodinamica. DreamCars muestra los supercoches ingleses mas fascinantes.

programme.title: Ford Mustang
programme.desc: Es el icono de todos los sedanes deportivos y descapotables. Ningun otro coche representa el estilo de vida de los 60 como el Ford Mustang. Con su diseno muy especial y su potente motor, el Mustang se gano el corazon de millones de entusiastas de los coches. La Historia del Automovil mostrara la historia del Ford Mustang, desde el primer prototipo hasta el ultimo Mustang Shelby de mas de 500 CV.

programme.title: Ano de Rallye 1972 - Una historia de exito de Ford
programme.desc: El campeonato internacional de fabricantes fue una serie de rallyes que se desarrollo entre 1970 y 72. Fabricantes de coches como Porsche, Renault y Ford participaron, con Ford teniendo un ano excepcionalmente exitoso en 1972.

programme.title: Stephane Peterhansel
programme.desc: El frances Stephane Peterhansel, ganador en 13 ocasiones del emblematico Rally Dakar, tuvo una carrera poco comun al sustituir las motos por los coches, pero cosechando grandes exitos en ambas modalidades. Tambien gano varias veces el Abu Dhabi Desert Challenge, anteriormente conocido como UAE Desert Challenge, tanto en moto como en rally.

programme.title: SUV Girlpower
programme.desc: Las pilotos jordanas Nancy y Nadia afrontaron el reto de cruzar el desierto marroqui en un Hummer H3. Las dos pilotos profesionales participaron en el Trofeo Conti 4x4, un agotador rally a traves del Atlas y el Sahara Occidental. Y ademas: dos de nuestras editoras prueban los todoterreno asiaticos SsangYong Rexton y Hyundai Grand Santa Fe; BMW X5 M: ¿un coche deportivo equipado como un SUV?

programme.title: Descapotables britanicos
programme.desc: Ya sea el Jaguar F-Type, el Aston Martin V8 Vantage o el Bentley Continental, los descapotables ingleses son elegantes y exclusivos. Los roadsters ingleses muestran autentica deportividad y disfrutan de estatus de culto mundial. La diversion con los biplazas abiertos y rapidos fue inventada en Inglaterra. DreamCars presenta los cabriolets ingleses mas impresionantes de todos los tiempos.

programme.title: Episodio 6
programme.desc: The Walk en JBR, el lugar mas prestigioso de Dubai, es el escenario de los coches customizados mas rapidos de Oriente Medio. Put Your Car on TV invita a los propietarios a exhibir sus coches. El propietario del coche mas rapido, bonito y con mejor sonido gana un premio especial del Sofitel Dubai Jumeirah Beach. Entre los competidores estan un Lamborghini Aventador y un Chevrolet GMC.

programme.title: Mini
programme.desc: Los Beatles, Peter Sellers, Britt Ekland o los Royals, todos ellos condujeron el Austin Mini. Disenado sobre una servilleta, el Mini 1959 comienza una trayectoria increible: el revolucionario y original Mini es considerado el prototipo de todo coche pequeno. La Historia del Automovil muestra toda la gran historia del Mini, desde el Mini original hasta el actual Rally-Mini.

programme.title: Alois Ruf
programme.desc: Alois Ruf es el fundador de una pequena pero conocida fabrica de coches de Baviera especializada en construir su propia version de coches deportivos, pero basandose en la carroceria de los Porsche.

programme.title: Prototipos SUV
programme.desc: Antes de que Bentley y Jaguar comenzaran a producir sus propios modelos de SUV de lujo, las dos marcas britanicas presentaron su version de esta gama especial de coches. Echamos un vistazo a sus coches prototipo: el Bentley EXP 9F y el C-X17 de Jaguar. Y ademas: ¿como ven los fabricantes japoneses como Toyota, Nissan o Subaru el futuro de los SUV?; el Unimog de Mercedes-Benz.

programme.title: Ferrari FF
programme.desc: El Ferrari FF es el gran auto deportivo familiar para todas las estaciones. Son dos cosas a la vez: un auto de carreras y una station wagon. Hasta la fecha, Ferrari es el unico que ha sabido combinar estas dos especies en un resultado de exito. Y es que FF es simplemente un auto hermoso, o como dirian los italianos, una "bella macchina".
